      <hedline>
        <hl1>Write 100 Times: Give Homework</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Letter from Greta H Kennedy, a high school teacher, commenting on Oct 10 article, says parents should realize that homework can support and enhance classroom teaching; drawing</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''As Homework Load Grows, One District Says 'Enough' '' (front page, Oct. 10):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''As Homework Load Grows, One District Says 'Enough' '' (front page, Oct. 10):</p>
        <p>The real problem today is the overscheduling of our children, not the fact that they get homework!</p>
        <p>How can we say education is our top priority and then limit teachers in assigning or even grading homework? This is a perfect example of the ''dumbing down'' of our schools.</p>
        <p>What happens when teachers' pay becomes linked to student performance? More than ever, teachers need the support of parents and the community.</p>
        <p>Homework cannot replace good teaching in the classroom, but it can support it and enhance learning. Parents need to decide what they want out of our schools and what they want for the future of our children and our country.</p>
        <p>GRETA H. KENNEDY  Roxbury, Conn., Oct. 11, 2000</p>
        <p>The writer is a high school teacher.</p>
      </block>
